Defendant Peter A Idsvoog in court with Attorney Jamie J LaVora.  Thomas L. Potter appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Matter is here for a Plea/Sentencing.  The defense is not readying to proceed with plea/sentencing today.  This is the second request for an adjournment from the defense.   The matter is going forward with a plea/sentencing today.

AS TO COUNT #1:    Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty.  Judgment of conviction entered.

AS TO COUNT #2:   Upon the State's Motion, this count is to be DISMISSED.  The Court ORDERED this count DISMISSED.
  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess any gun or other firearms. 
Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.  
Court advised that the defendant will have to provide a DNA sample, to the Wisconsin State Crime Laboratory for DNA testing and pay a DNA surcharge.
Appeal Rights Given

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

The Court imposed the following sentence:
   
AS TO COUNT #1:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be THIRTY-NINE (39) months.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for FIFTEEN (15) months with credit for TWO (2) days time served.  Defendant shall serve TWENTY-FOUR (24) months on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.    Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.

The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  
The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Absolute Sobriety;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Interlock Device for THIRTY-SIX months;
 - Operating Privileges suspended for THIRTY-SIX (36) months from today's date with $60 reinstatement fee;
 - Pay fine in the amount of $2,400.  Bail applied to fine first and then balance of cost as part of condition of supervision;
 - 75 hours of Community Service.  Defendant to speak with others who have addictions issues.


Filed,
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
